						<summary>

						<p>This consists of two parts and is much damaged. Its date is lost but it refers itself to the reign of the Chāḷukya king <hi rend="bold">Tribhuvanamalladēva</hi> and mentions his subordinate <hi rend="italic">Mahāmaṇḍalesvara</hi> <hi rend="bold">Śaṅkaradēva.</hi> From the second part it appears that a gift of land was made.</p>						

						<p>First Piece.</p>						

						</summary>
